<HEAD>Maltese Leader Opens US Talks</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Maltese Prime Minister Eddie Fenech Adami will
be meeting with President Reagan on Wednesday as part of that
Mediterranean island nation's drive to improve ties with the West.
   The meeting will be the first meeting between a Maltese prime
minister and an American president in 19 years. Fenech Adami is
visiting other U.S. officials, and on Monday met with Deputy
Secretary of State John C. Whitehead.
   Fenech Adami, a Christian Democrat, was elected last year after
16 years of Socialist rule. Under former Prime Minister Don
Mintoff, Malta strengthened its bonds with Communist nations and
with Libya, which the United States has attacked as a supporter of
terrorism.
   Mintoff also tried to persuade European countries to exert
diplomatic pressure on Israel in its disputes with Arab neighbors.
