<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Soiled Skirt,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Billed 180 Motels For Cleaning Skirt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man has been sentenced to four years in prison
after he pleaded guilty to bilking more than 180 Holiday Inn motels
out of $6,000 to clean a mythical soiled suede skirt.
   U.S. District Judge Zita Weinshienk also sentenced Keith W.
Froemming to five years probation on Monday and ordered him to pay
$443.08 in restitution and $100 to a crime victims' fund.
   Froemming, who is from Vail, was accused of mailing letters to
more than 180 Holiday Inn motels contending that a waiter spilled
coffee on his wife's suede skirt. He enclosed a purported cleaning
bill for $30.16.
   Froemming and his associate, Joan Atwell, allegedly received 200
checks worth more than $6,000 from the motels, federal records
indicate.
   Froemming pleaded guilty to two counts of mail-fraud.
   As a condition of probation, Weinshienk ordered Froemming to
attend Gamblers Anonymous meetings and to stay away from Las Vegas,
Nev.
   Atwell was sentenced to four years' probation, and ordered to
pay a $1,000 fine and make restitution in a June 27 sentencing.
