<HEAD>Eight Prospectors Killed In Search of Gold, Others Trapped</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOGOTA, Colombia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mudslide in a shallow mine killed
eight prospectors and trapped at least eight others while they were
digging for gold in the town of Taraza, the mayor said today.
   Rogelio Osorio, mayor of Taraza, said the accident occurred
Monday afternoon when soil softened by rain slid into the shaft and
enveloped the prospectors.
   Police said they rescued one man and pulled eight bodies out of
the mud, but that at least eight others were trapped and believed
dead.
   Last week, 10 miners died in a similar accident near Taraza, a
town north of Bogota.
   The mayor said about 2,000 farmers had come to the area in
search of gold in mines unprotected by safety measures.
</TEXT>
