<1ST_LINE>d a PM-BRF--LaundryShooting     07-12 0152</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-BRF--Laundry Shooting,0155</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Nine People Wounded in Harlem Laundry</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A dispute erupted at a coin-operated laundry
after a customer complained of losing 75 cents in a machine, and
nine people suffered minor gunshot wounds, police said.
   Three people were arrested in connection with the incident
Monday night at a laundry in Harlem.
   According to Officer Peter O'Donnell, a police spokesman, the
incident started when Nicole Nixon, 18, argued with a laundry
attendant after losing money in a machine. Miss Nixon was hit in
the head and was taken to Harlem Hospital, he said.
   About an hour later, police said, Miss Nixon's mother,
stepfather, 10-year-old brother and boyfriend showed up, and
another dispute erupted. One or two people fired an undetermined
number of shots, he said.
   Those wounded included Miss Nixon's relatives and boyfriend, and
some bystanders on the street, according to Sgt. Ed Burns, another
police spokesman.
</TEXT>
