<1ST_LINE>r i PM-China-Landslide     07-12 0129</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-China-Landslide,0136</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Mudslide Kills 35 In Southwest China</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mudslide killed 35 workers at a power station
in southwest China, where flooding after heavy rains has already
claimed 76 lives, the official Xinhua News Agency reported today.
   The slide also injured 10 workers when it swept through the
electric generating plant in the Liangshan Yi region of Sichuan
province Sunday evening, the agency said. The report said one
person was missing.
   Last week, 11 people died in flooding in Sichuan province after
more than 20 inches of rain fell in two days. In late June, 65
people were reported dead after a heavy rainfall.
   Also last week, a landslide caused by rain in northwest Gansu
province killed 41 people, destroyed homes and caused power
failures.
</TEXT>
