<HEAD>New Orleans Morgue Refrigerators Break Down</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Nine of the 11 refrigerators in the city
morgue broke again, and the stench of decomposing bodies filled the
courthouse.
   ``The boxes are old and they are constantly going out. Three
went out last week and over the weekend another six went out,''
said chief coroner's investigator John Gagliano.
   Four unidentified, decomposing bodies remained despite the
broken refrigerators because they were not be accepted by a
hospital, he said.
   Gagliano said the coroner's office has been waiting for the city
to install a walk-in cooler, approved by voters 2{ years ago in a
bond issue. ``The city's dragging its feet,'' he said.
   But Assistant Chief Administrative Officer Leonard Simmons said
the administration of Mayor Sidney Barthelemy is not to blame. Work
would be further along if the coroner's office hadn't insisted on
design changes, he said.
