<HEAD>Seven Dead, 32 Missing In Pakistan Boat Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>KARACHI, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A sailboat carrying 55 people home from
a wedding capsized in the Indus River near Sakkur, and an official
said on Tuesday that seven passengers were killed and 32 missing.
   Roshen Zamire, commissioner of Sukkur, said seven bodies were
recovered after Monday's accident and that the 32 missing people
were presumed drowned. He said 16 passengers swam safely to shore.
   The Indus River was swollen at the time by heavy rains and
spring runoff from mountains to the north, he said.
   The wedding took place in the village of Kashmore, 60 miles from
Sukkur.
