<HEAD>14 Killed, 34 Injured In Bus Accident In Taiwan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>TAIPEI, Taiwan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A bus packed with hikers plunged off a
mountain highway Tuesday in northern Taiwan, killing at least 14
passengers and injuring 34, police said.
   The bus tumbled 200 feet down a deep valley from a steep road in
Balin, Taoyuan, 30 miles south of Taipei, police said.
   Taoyuan police reported 14 people died, but the Central News
Agency put the death toll at 17. The police, who spoke on condition
of anonymity, said about 10 of the injured people were seriously
hurt.
   Police said the bus, which was more than 10 years old, did not
have enough power to climb the mountain road and slid back,
tumbling into the valley.
   The bus was carrying the Taiwanese passengers to a mountain stop
from where they were to begin hiking, police said. There were no
foreigners on the bus.
</TEXT>
