   The father of the Osmond family singers is
home recuperating from a truck accident after an overnight hospital
stay.
   George Osmond, 70, was released Monday from Utah Valley Regional
Medical Center. He escaped serious injury Sunday when the brakes on
his pickup apparently failed as he was driving down a hill and the
vehicle climbed a 15-foot embankment and overturned.
   Osmond's wife, Olive, was following behind in a car. After he
crawled out, she took him to the hospital.
