<HEAD>In Movie, Reagan's Post-White House Office Blown Up by Terrorists</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The building that will house President
Reagan's post-White House office is blown up by terrorists _ in a
new movie.
   Last week, officials of the Ronald Reagan Presidential
Foundation disclosed Reagan will have an office on the 34th floor
of Century City's fashionable Fox Plaza tower after he leaves
office in January. The foundation also has offices on that floor.
   The Reagans will live in nearby Bel-Air.
   Fox Plaza is the high-rise used by 20th Century Fox in ``Die
Hard,'' an upcoming movie that shows terrorists penetrating secret
entrances and air conditioning ducts, ``the real guts of the
building,'' studio spokeswoman Sharon Holliday said Tuesday.
   In the movie, the terrorists eventually blow up the building.
   The Secret Service, which will continue to guard Reagan when he
leaves office, wouldn't comment on the film or on any security
precautions, said a duty officer reached in Los Angeles, who
refused to give his name.
   In the movie, Bruce Willis portrays a New York policeman who
goes to Los Angeles to try to patch up his crumbling marriage. The
terrorists take over the building during an office Christmas party
Willis attends with his estranged wife.
   The movie is being released in major cities this weekend and
nationwide on July 20.
