<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Semiconductor     07-12 0156</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Semiconductor,0163</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Intel Reports 181 Percent Earnings Gain, Record Revenues</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SANTA CLARA, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Intel Corp.'s profit nearly tripled
in the last quarter as revenue rose 66 percent, the company said
Tuesday.
   Intel's net income for the quarter was $131 million, or 73 cents
a share, an increase of 181 percent from $46 million, or 25 cents a
share, for last year's second quarter, the company said.
   Revenue rose to $727 million from $439 million a year earlier.
   ``This was a quarter for broad-based growth,'' Andrew S. Grove,
Intel's president and chief executive, said in a statement. ``The
strength of the personal computer and workstation markets continues
to drive our growth.''
   For the first six months of its fiscal year, Intel said its
profit rose to $224 million, or $1.27 a share, from $72 million, or
39 cents a share, a year earlier. Revenue rose to $1.36 billion
from $833 million a year earlier.
</TEXT>
