<2ND_LINE>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0406</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Stock prices fell today as investors showed
concern over interest rates and the trade deficit.
   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials was off 20.63 points to
2,090.68 with an hour left to go on Wall Street.
   Losers outnumbered gainers more than 7 to 2 in the overall tally
of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 364 up, 1,063 down
and 466 unchanged.
   Volume on the Big Board, swollen by dividend-related trading,
came to 139.47 million shares as of 3 p.m. on Wall Street.
   Stock market investors have dwelled lately on the possibility
that the Federal Reserve will push up interest rates as a way to
cool the economy and stave off inflation.
   Concerns about rising interest rates have dampened the stock
market because more attractive yields on bonds could siphon money
away from stocks. Also, high rates could hurt stock prices by
slowing economic growth.
   ``This is a market that's back-pedaling,'' said Alan Ackerman,
an investment strategist for Gruntal & Co. ``Anxiety over higher
interest rates is keeping players on the sidelines as well as
stalling some of the summer sizzle that appears to lie ahead.''
   Traders also appeared cautious in advance of Friday's release of
figures on the May merchandise trade deficit.
   The heaviest trading was related to dividend-capture strategies.
Centerior Energy had more than 9 million shares change hands in
early trading. Puget Sound Power & Light and New York State
Electric & Gas each had more than 4 million shares traded.
   Coleco Industries sank { to 1]. The company announced it had
sought protection from creditors under Chapter 11 of the Bankruptcy
Code.
   Xidex rose 1\ to 8~ in heavy over-the-counter trading of more
than 3.8 million shares. The maker of computer disk drives said it
agreed to be acquired by Anacomp for $10 a share in cash. Anacomp
was off 1 to 10 on the NYSE in heavy trading.
   Among other over-the-counter stocks, Intel was up ~ to 35{ on
heavy trading after reporting its earnings nearly tripled in the
latest quarter. Micron Technology was off } to 23[ on news that two
top officers resigned.
   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocks fell
1.46 to 151.56. At the American Stock Exchange, the market value
index fell 1.73 to 306.85.
