<FILEID>AP-NR-07-12-88 2249EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f AM-Earns-ICIndustries     07-12 0204</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Earns-IC Industries,0212</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Reports 21 Percent Gain in 2nd Quarter Profit</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   IC Industries, the diversified producer of Pet
food products and Midas mufflers, said Tuesday its second-quarter
profit climbed 21 percent on an 18 percent revenue gain.
   IC reported net income of $55.8 million, or 52 cents a share,
for the three months ended June 30, compared with $46 million, or
41 cents a share, for the same period a year ago.
   Second-quarter revenue increased to $857.7 million from $729
million, the company said.
   IC's soft-drinks division, including its Pepsi-Cola General
Bottlers joint venture with Pepsico Inc., was the most improved
sector with sales of nearly $237 million, a 54 percent increase
from a year ago.
   The earnings include the results of two companies listed by IC
as discontinued operations: the Illinois Central Railroad Co.,
which is being spun off as a separate company; and Pneumo Abex, an
aircraft-parts maker, which is being sold.
   For the first six months of this year, IC had net income of
$96.5 million, or 90 cents a share, compared with net income of
$74.9 million, or 66 cents a share, a year earlier.
   First-half sales rose to $1.6 billion from $1.4 billion in 1987.
</TEXT>
